\pard\plain \ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 He smiled at the thought that he could mean such different thigns to different people, and he sobbed at the realization that all he was, and all he\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92d ever been, was that very difference. And once his dissembled self had been reduced to the sum of shifting differences between perceptions in other people, he began to sneak into apotheosis as a .}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 He was here, all of him, and as he did not end, all of him meant every thing. He was stomach and skin, fingers and toes, the wind, dust swimming in beads of rain.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 But this could not be true.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 It was absurd.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 He was Mandrameen.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 He needed a word to define it, without a word he would succumb to the passion without seeing it, as any dog would. It would be invisible to him without a word. He coudl anchor no  strartegy without a word. A word was brick to build with. A stone to throw. A leap to close distance, a pull to open up. And with a word is space, to keep things separate, for without separation it would all run ajumble and the fragile order imparted on the world through language would fall apart.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Behold, Mandrameen!}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Breaker of worlds.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Maker of words.}}